
---


@startuml

' Define classes and their attributes

class Location {
    +id: int
    +name: String
    +description: String
}

class Exhibition {
    +id: int
    +title: String
    +startDate: Date
    +endDate: Date
}

class Employee {
    +id: int
    +name: String
    +role: String
}

class ExhibitionItem {
    +id: int
    +description: String
    +criteria: String
}

class Piece {
    +id: int
    +title: String
    +artist: String
    +period: String
}

class Collector {
    +id: int
    +name: String
    +contactInfo: String
}

' Relationships

Location "1" -- "0..*" Exhibition : contains
Exhibition "1" -- "1" Employee : has coordinator
Exhibition "1" -- "1..*" ExhibitionItem : includes
ExhibitionItem "1" -- "1..*" Piece : has candidate pieces
Piece "1" -- "1" Collector : owned by
Employee "1" -- "0..*" Employee : coaches > (coach)
Employee "1" -- "0..1" Employee : is coached by < (junior)

@enduml

---

### 🧾 Explanation of Classes and Relationships:

- **`Location`**: A physical area within the museum that can host one or more exhibitions.
- **`Exhibition`**: An event hosted in a specific location, with a start and end date. Each exhibition has exactly one **coordinator** (`Employee`) and consists of multiple **ExhibitionItems**.
- **`Employee`**: Represents museum staff. Some are **coaches** to other employees, forming a mentoring relationship.
- **`ExhibitionItem`**: A desired item for an exhibition (e.g., "a sunflower painting"). Each item may have several **candidate Pieces**.
- **`Piece`**: A specific artwork or object that is being considered for inclusion in an exhibition. Owned by a **Collector**.
- **`Collector`**: An individual or institution that owns art pieces available for possible loan.

